            <h2>Introduction</h2>
            <p>This section demonstrates how padding, borders, and margins work together in the CSS Box Model. You can see the effect of each property visually.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="card highlight">
            <h2>Box Model Parts</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Content:</strong> The text, image, or other media inside the box.</li>
                <li><strong>Padding:</strong> Space between content and the border.</li>
                <li><strong>Border:</strong> The edge around the element.</li>
                <li><strong>Margin:</strong> Space between this element and other elements.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="card">
            <h2>Styled Button</h2>
            <button class="btn-primary">Click Me</button>
        </section>
